## State Management Best Practices

### State Placement
```typescript
// ✅ Local state (component-specific)
function RecordingTimer() {
  const [seconds, setSeconds] = useState(0)  // ✅ Only used here
  // ...
}

// ✅ Context state (shared across multiple components)
// RecordingContext provides isRecording, audioPath, etc.

// ✅ IPC state (main process is source of truth)
// Recordings list, settings, etc. — fetch from main via IPC
```

### Avoid Prop Drilling
```typescript
// ❌ Prop drilling (passing props through 5 levels)
<App isRecording={isRecording}>
  <Layout isRecording={isRecording}>
    <Sidebar isRecording={isRecording}>
      <RecordingStatus isRecording={isRecording} />
    </Sidebar>
  </Layout>
</App>

// ✅ Use context instead
const { isRecording } = useRecording()  // Access anywhere
```

### Derived State
```typescript
// ❌ Redundant state
const [recordings, setRecordings] = useState([])
const [recordingCount, setRecordingCount] = useState(0)  // ❌ Derived from recordings

// ✅ Compute derived state
const [recordings, setRecordings] = useState([])
const recordingCount = recordings.length  // ✅ No separate state needed

// ✅ Use useMemo for expensive computations
const sortedRecordings = useMemo(() => {
  return [...recordings].sort((a, b) => b.createdAt - a.createdAt)
}, [recordings])
```

