## Forbidden Patterns (React/TypeScript)

### ❌ Never Do This
```typescript
// 1. `any` type
function process(data: any) { ... }  // ❌

// 2. `require()` in renderer (ESM only)
const fs = require('fs')  // ❌ Use import

// 3. Direct `ipcRenderer` in renderer
import { ipcRenderer } from 'electron'  // ❌ Use window.api.*

// 4. Inline styles
<div style={{ color: 'red' }}>  // ❌ Use Tailwind classes

// 5. Class components
class MyComponent extends React.Component { ... }  // ❌ Use function components

// 6. Uncontrolled components without ref
<input defaultValue="test" />  // ❌ Use controlled (value + onChange)

// 7. Index as key in lists
{items.map((item, index) => <div key={index}>)}  // ❌ Use unique ID

// 8. Mutating state directly
state.items.push(newItem)  // ❌ Use setState with new array

// 9. Side effects in render
function Component() {
  window.api.doSomething()  // ❌ Use useEffect
  return <div>...</div>
}

// 10. Non-memoized callbacks as props
<Child onClick={() => doSomething()} />  // ❌ Child re-renders every time
```

### ✅ Do This Instead
```typescript
// 1. Proper types or `unknown`
function process(data: RecordingData | unknown) { ... }  // ✅

// 2. ESM imports
import fs from 'fs'  // ✅

// 3. Use exposed API
window.api.readFile(path)  // ✅

// 4. Tailwind classes
<div className="text-red-500">  // ✅

// 5. Function components
function MyComponent() { ... }  // ✅

// 6. Controlled components
<input value={value} onChange={(e) => setValue(e.target.value)} />  // ✅

// 7. Unique ID as key
{items.map((item) => <div key={item.id}>)}  // ✅

// 8. Immutable state updates
setState(prev => [...prev, newItem])  // ✅

// 9. Side effects in useEffect
useEffect(() => {
  window.api.doSomething()
}, [])  // ✅

// 10. Memoized callbacks
const handleClick = useCallback(() => doSomething(), [])
<Child onClick={handleClick} />  // ✅
```

